name: orbencarb production | orbencarb | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/8050/documentation

This dataset represents the production of orbencarb (1 kg of active ingredient). Raw materials are modelled with a stoichiometric calculation.  Energy consumption is modelled with data from a similar process. The emissions are estimated. Infrastructure is included with a default value.;This dataset represents the production of orbencarb (1 kg of active ingredient). Raw materials are modelled with a stoichiometric calculation.  Energy consumption is modelled with data from a similar process. The emissions are estimated. Infrastructure is included with a default value.

From reception of precursors (bromine, carbon monoxide, chlorine, ethylenediamine, sodium hydroxide, sulfur, toluene, and "water, salt, sole") at the factory gate.

This activity ends with  orbencarb at the factory gate. The dataset includes the input materials, energy uses, infrastructure and emissions. The dataset doesn't include emulsives, additives etc.
category: C:Manufacturing/20:Manufacture of chemicals and chemical products/202:Manufacture of other chemical products/2021:Manufacture of pesticides and other agrochemical products

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: The inventory is modelled for Europe.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Orbencarb is a pesticide produced in two steps from diethyl amine:;C4H11N + COS → C5H11NOS;C5H11NOS + C7H6ClBr → C12H16ClNOS + HBr;Precursors that are used for the orbencarb production are carbonyl sulfide (COS) and 2-chloro benzyl bromide (C7H6ClBr).;Carbonyl sulfide (COS) is produced from carbon monoxide and sulfur:;CO + S → COS;2-Chloro benzyl bromide (C7H6ClBr) is produced in two steps from toluene:;C7H8 + Cl2 → C7H7Cl + HCl;C7H7Cl + Br2 → C7H6ClBr + HBr

exchanges.description:
EcoSpold01Location=RER
Orbencarb is a colourless liquid which is moderately soluble in water and readily soluble in most organic solvents.
The name "orthobencarb" is approved by the Japanese Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries.
Orbencarb is a selective herbicide used pre-emergence to control broad-leaved weeds in barley, wheat, rye, maize, soya beans, cotton, and turf.

exchanges.description:
EcoSpold01Location=UCTE
Estimation, assuming a default value, originated from calculation of avarage consumption of electricity and heat per kg of product (3.2 MJ kg-1), and a resulting amount of electricity of 0,333 kW for every reaction step per kg reaction product, considering that the demand is made up of a mix that inlcudes 38% electricity.  Additionally, reaction steps are approximated with energy consumption data, assuming that inventory flows can be estimated using process data for basic operation steps, available for specific organic chemicals.

Further references:

Kim S., Overcash M.: Energy in chemical manufacturing processes: gate-to-gate information for life cycle assessment. In: Journal of Chemical Technology & Biotechnology vol. 78,  no. 9: 995-1005(11). 2003
